Commentary.Commentary: The players are back on the field! Rohit Sharma and KL Rahul are the Indian openers. Here is James Anderson running in his favourite overcast conditions. Let's play...

Right then, the Indian bowlers have done their job efficiently and it's now the turn of their batters to back up the good work. A little over 20 overs left in the day's play and expect England to come out all guns blazing. The conditions have offered movement throughout the day and it's going to be a stern test for the Indian batting unit. Stay tuned for their reply.

From 138/3, it was a collapse of epic proportions for England. As soon as Jonny Bairstow departed, the floodgates opened. It was a steady procession of wickets as the Indian bowlers got into the act. A complete team performance from the visiting side. Mohammed Shami was a shade unlucky in the morning session but then bounced back superbly to pick three wickets. Mohammed Siraj and Shardul Thakur also contributed to the cause.

It was all India after Tea. The first two sessions were shared but by snapping 6 wickets in the evening, the tourists have gained the upper hand in this Test match. Electing to bat first, as a team, England will be disappointed to get a paltry score on the board in the first innings. Only Joe Root managed to stand out with his knock and his partnership with Bairstow was the only substantial stand that the hosts managed.

India have finally managed to break the stubborn last-wicket resistance between Sam Curran and James Anderson. Jasprit Bumrah finishes with a 4-wicket haul and it's a great effort from the Indian team after losing the toss in the morning.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! If not on the previous ball, then now, says Bumrah. Brilliant delivery and India will be mighty pleased with their work so far. Jasprit Bumrah steams in and fires another yorker, this time, at the base of the off pole, James Anderson is years late to get his bat down, as the ball crashes into the furniture behind. A smile on Anderson's face. A smile on Bumrah's face as well. ENGLAND END ON 183!
Commentary.Howout: b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: NOT OUT! The review saves Anderson and the wait for India to end the innings continues. Serves a yorker, right at the base of middle and leg, Anderson looks to dig it out but misses and the ball hits his boot. An appeal and the finger goes up. James Anderson takes the review. No bat on this, as it hit the boot first. Ball Tracker shows that the trajectory of the ball was moving away from the sticks and it would go onto miss the leg pole. Decision overturned.

Finger has gone up! Anderson is given out lbw as he is struck flush on the right boot. DRS taken. It's boot first, the replays confirm. The Ball Tracker comes now... It's MISSING WICKETS. Anderson can continue batting.
Good length this time, around off, pushed to the leg side.
Fuller ball, outside off, James looks to have a poke at this but misses. So close for India and Bumrah...
Jasprit Bumrah has got six balls at James Anderson.

FOUR! Another boundary to end the over. India are not able to find the final wicket and this partnership continues to grow. On a fuller length, around off, Sam Curran makes room and lofts this one over point. Takes a couple of bounces and goes past the ropes.
They take the single here! Around off, this is nudged through mid-wicket. They take one and Jimmy wants another, but it is not available here.
PLAY AND A MISS! A length delivery, outside off, James Anderson looks to drive this one, but the ball evades his bat, and its edge, to go to the keeper.
Digs in a short ball, way outside off, James Anderson just lets it be.
Angles a length delivery around off, James pushes it to short mid on. No run taken again. Shami would fancy his chances against Jimmy!
A length ball, outside off, shaping inwards, James Anderson looks to push but gets beaten.
FOUR! The ball will run away to the boundary, but they have James Anderson on strike in the next over. Outside off, on a length, moving away, Sam Curran thumps this one through covers for a boundary.
Looked to be trying something else, but Bumrah serves a full toss on middle, Sam Curran punches this one to the cover fielder.
Outside off, Curran wants to leave this, but leaves his bat hanging. The ball takes the bat and goes down to the third man region. No run taken again.
On a length this time, going down leg, Curran looks to tuck, but the ball takes the pad and goes on the bounce to the right of Pant, who moves that side and stops the ball well.
A length delivery, around off, Sam Curran pushes the ball back to the bowler.
Sam Curran makes room and Bumrah follows him with an inswinging ball around middle and leg, Curran punches it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on middle and off, Anderson defends it from the back foot and the crowd loved it.

'CATCH IT'...the ball falls just short. Fuller in length around off, moving away, Curran tries heaving but gets a top edge down to third man. Hanuma Vihari (sub) comes running in, puts in a dive as well but it falls in front of him. The batsmen jog across for a single.
Thakur tries for a yorker but serves a full toss instead, it's outside off, Curran hangs back and goes hard at it. Fails to middle his shot and hits it to mid off.
FOUR! In the slot and Curran has dismissed it. A proper heave. Fuller in length and around leg, Curran clears his front leg and powers it over mid-wicket for a boundary. The score moves to 173/9!
A touch short again, around middle and leg, Curran moves back and guides it to deep point. Turns down the single.
Short in length and on off, Curran punches it off his back foot but finds the tumbling cover fielder.
Survives! Full and around off, shaping away, Anderson pushes inside the line and misses.

Curran does find it! Fullish and on middle, Sam works it to the left of mid on and scampers across to the other end. Hang on, it's called a no ball and Bumrah has one extra ball up his sleeves. Anderson on strike!
Good length ball on off, Curran pushes it from the back foot to covers. Now then, can Sam find a single on the final ball?
Bumrah gets in the line of the stumps, full and around leg, Curran defends it back to the bowler.
An outswinger, on a good length around off, Curran covers his stumps and lets it be.
Identical to the last delivery, Curran is not going after it as of now.
Slightly short in length and close to off, shaping away, Curran remains on the back foot and shoulders arms.
Curran gets the desired result on the final ball. He fetches a short ball from outside off and hooks it in front of square leg for a single. Keeps strike with himself.
Swing and a miss! A length ball landing on middle, Curran tees off for a big heave-ho over the leg side but fails to connect. It goes over the stumps to the keeper.
Good length delivery on middle and off, Curran stays on the back foot and taps it down to point. He is not trying for singles.
Shardul goes fuller and on middle, Curran defends it from the back foot to mid off.

SIX! Sam Curran has decided to cut loose! Back of a length delivery around off, Curran hangs back inside the crease and hammers it all the way over long on for a biggie. He has the license now to play the big shots.
Beats the bat! Fuller in length and around off, angling away, Curran hangs his bat out aimlessly and gets beaten.
James Anderson walks in next.

OUT! Broad is a dead duck! Bumrah bowls a very full ball on middle and leg at 87.9 kph, Broad is sitting way too deep inside the crease, probably expecting a bouncer, and as a result, he is late in bringing his bat down. The ball strikes him on the back pad and you cannot get more plumb than this. Just one wicket left for England.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Too full in length and outside off, Sam drives it through covers for a single.
Superb delivery, speedy and around leg on a length, Curran tries to flick but misses and it clips his pads on its way to the keeper.
Bumrah attempts for an inswinger but ends up serving it way down the leg side, Curran tries flicking but misses.
Spears in a fuller length ball on middle and off, a hint of away shape, Curran sticks on the back foot and pushes it out defensively to covers.
Good length ball on off, angling in, Curran stays back and defends it to the off side.
A length ball outside off, angling away, Broad lets it be. End of a superb over by Thakur.
FOUR! Stuart Broad does not take long to get going. Fuller in length, outside off, Stuart Broad just drives this one crisply through covers and the ball speeds away to the ropes.

OUT! Caught at mid on! Two wickets in the over for Shardul and he is pumped up! A harmless delivery, bowled short around off at 79 mph, Robinson goes on his toes to pull but ends up getting a top edge to mid on. Mohammed Shami accepts the catch gleefully and England are in complete disarray.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammed Shami b Shardul Thakur

Commentary.Commentary: England have just 2 more batters remaining now. The first of which, Stuart Broad is in now!
On a length and outside off, shaping away, Ollie allows it through to the keeper.
Fuller in length around off, Robinson gets on the front foot and pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! Shardul returns and takes out the big fish! Root is disappointed, shakes his head, looks at his partner who conveys the message that you are trapped in front. This is a beautiful delivery by Thakur. A dream one. He delivers an outswinger on a fuller length around leg, Root fails to flick and is pinged on the pads. They appeal and the umpire has no hesitation in lifting his finger. Joe knows that he is a goner and returns. This is a body blow to England. Their skipper, who was batting so well, has been uprooted from the crease. England are 155/7!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Shardul Thakur

Commentary.Commentary: Ollie Robinson walks out.
On a length around middle and off, Curran goes on the back foot and blocks it down safely.
Inswinger this time! Bumrah spears it in, around middle and leg, Curran is beaten completely and is pinged on the pads.
Action replay of the second delivery. Curran is opened up in his defense as he tries to block and the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
Fullish and on middle, again moving away, Curran blocks it towards mid off.
Beaten! Bumrah's 'round the wicket angle is troubling the left-hander. It's around off, Sam tries defending the line but it nips away to beat the outside edge.

FOUR! Controlled edge? Back of a length ball on top of off, Curran remains on the back foot and pushes inside the line at the last moment. He does so with soft hands and the outside edge screams past the slip cordon for a boundary at third man.

FOUR! Fine pull shot from the English skipper. Siraj digs in a short ball around off, Joe Root swivels on the back foot and hooks it behind square leg. It beats the fielder in the deep to his right and finds the fence. 150 comes up for England.
Bouncer around off, Joe drops his wrists and sways away. Pant jumps to collect the ball.
A length ball on off, Root stays back and defends it to the off side.

Australia? More like Loss-tralia. Bangladesh, who had won the first T20I of the series yesterday against Australia, have bettered their performance and have won the second T20I by 5 wickets. They also take a 2-0 lead in the 5-game T20I series. Some work to be done by the Aussies, if they want to avoid losing the next game, and potentially, the series.
Fractionally short in length and on off, Curran hangs back and plays it down with soft hands to point for a brisk run. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but Root is easily in.
Shortish and close to off, Root plays it late as he goes on the back foot and taps it down to backward point for one.
Good length delivery outside off, Root shows no interest in playing at it.
Change. Mohammed Siraj comes back on. 11-2-42-1 so far.
Bumrah runs in from 'round the wicket for the left-hander and delivers a length ball on off, Curran stays back to defend and does so from the outer half of his blade. Fantastic over by Bumrah.
Sam Curran arrives into the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! This was always on the card as Jos Buttler was getting restless. Bumrah knew the state of Buttler's mind. The batter was trying to feel the ball and Jasprit served one for him on the plate outside off. The English wicketkeeper found the delivery to be in his zone and once again attempted for a booming cover drive. But it's not that easy to do it against the moving ball. Buttler's front foot goes nowhere, only his flashy blade comes down and as a result, a thick outside edge is generated. Rishabh Pant makes no mistake and Jos is dismissed for an 18-ball duck.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Bumrah goes even wider outside off, asking the batsman to reach for it, this time Buttler shows restraint and allows it through.
Comprehensively beaten! Bumrah serves it full and wide outside off, Buttler aims for a booming cover drive but fails to connect. Jos is getting restless, he has faced 16 balls for nothing.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Joe sticks back and guides it past gully. There is a third man fielder in place, so only a run.
Movement again for the bowler. We are into the 56th over but the ball is still moving around. Good length and outside off, nipping in off the pitch, Root pokes at it tentatively and gets beaten.
Outside off, on a length, shouldered arms to.
Fuller this time, on off, Buttler presents a straight bat and pushes to mid off. Looks for the run, but it is not available there.
Around the off pole, Jos pushes it to point.
An away swinger outside off, Buttler maintains social distancing and leaves it.
Tries to bowl the inswinger, but strays and bowls it on the pads, Root flicks it to fine leg and rotates the strike.
Good length around off, kept out.
Around off, defended watchfully. Jos Buttler has faced 11 balls but is yet to open his account.

A wonderful delivery and good glovework by Rishabh behind too. After a couple of length balls, Bumrah fires in a yorker, just outside off, Buttler looks to dig it out, but he misses and Rishabh Pant dives to his left and grabs the cherry.
Outside off, on a length, Buttler does not bother chasing after this.
Quicker, coming in, around off, Jos blocks well.
Angles across a length ball, coming in, Jos Buttler hops and looks to defend, but the ball goes past him, to the keeper. There was some sound but not sure from where it came.

Width offered outside off, length ball, JB slaps this one aerially towards backward point. The ball bounces as it looks to be evading Jadeja, but RJ does well to stretch his left hand and stop the ball with a full length dive.
FOUR! Beautiful boundary. A half-volley, outside off, Joe Root's eyes lit up as he creams this one through covers, beating the fielder in the deep to his right.
Length around off, tapped to point.
Inswinger around off and middle, knocked to the leg side.

Another example of how well Shami is bowling. Root is still not able to play at his best against Shami. On a length again, around off, some away shape again and the ball flashes past the outside edge of Root's bat, to the keeper.
Back of a length this time, outside off, Root dabs it down towards point.
On a length, outside off, stays a touch low as Root leaves it.
Angled into the body, nudged to the leg side. Tidy stuff from Jasprit Bumrah!
Angles another good length delivery, around off. Jos Buttler gets back and blocks well.
BEATEN! Brilliant. Not letting Jos settle in. Angles a length delivery, outside off, the ball shapes away late and misses Buttler's poking blade.
Short of a length ball this time, angling around middle and leg, Jos Buttler looks to work it to the leg side, but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Well fielded by the man there. Fuller, around off, Buttler drives this one to the left of mid off, who shuffles quickly and dives to stop the ball.
Outside off, cut through point for a single.
Jos Buttler arrives at number 7.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! That is the second wicket in the over and Lawrence goes back for a duck here. Not the best delivery, but still, Shami strikes here. India, have started all the sessions with a wicket to their name, and the third one is no exception. Mohammed Shami hurls across a length ball, but it is sliding down the leg side. Dan Lawrence gets across the stumps and looks to clip, but only manages a thin edge. Rishabh Pant moves to his left and pouches this. An appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Dan Lawrence shakes his head as he walks back. Does not opt for the review as he probably knew that he edged this. Half the English side is back in the shed and India will look to make further inroads here.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Serves a fuller ball now, sliding down leg, Dan Lawrence looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length, around off, Lawrence pushes this to mid on and yells no for the run.
Bowls a fuller length ball, around off, Dan pushes this to the cover region.

We're back! The men concerned are out in the middle. We have got a long post-Tea session in front of us. 38.4 overs to be bowled. Dan Lawrence has joined Joe Root in the middle and it will be Mohammed Shami to complete his over.
... DAY 1, 3RD SESSION ...

That wicket of Jonny Bairstow has brought the smiles back in the Indian dressing room. It was yet another hard-fought session of Test cricket. India initiated it by dismissing Dominic Sibley quickly but then witnessed a stern resistance from the pair of Joe Root and Jonny Bairstow. They mixed caution with aggression in their approach and never got bogged down. India did bowl well but without much success throughout the session and had they not got Bairstow at the stroke of Tea, it would have worried them. The unlucky bowler of the morning session, Mohammed Shami, bagged both the wickets to fall in the afternoon. This Test match is nicely hanging in the balance with both teams standing on even ground. Who will gain the upper hand in the last session? Do join us at 3 pm GMT (4 pm local) to find out.

Huge shout for an lbw! Not given. Is it bat first or pad? The Ultra Edge detects a flat line. The Ball Tracker shows that it's HITTING THE LEG STUMP! The onfield decision is overturned and India have a breakthrough right at the fag end of this session.

OUT! LBW! That is another great review for India and they have struck right at the stroke of Tea. That's the end of Jonny Bairstow and this stand, worth 72 runs, which was looking very good has been cut short by Shami. This is served on a length, around off. The ball jags back in and seems to have taken some part of the bat, before pinging Bairstow on the pad. An appeal but the umpire says no. The Indian players converge and there is a discussion here, if they should take the review now or not. Virat Kohli is seen asking if there was any bat on this. The player on the receiving end of the question says he does not think there was any bat. Kohli confirms again and is still not sure, but in the end, goes for it. Ultra Edge shows no spike, as the ball goes past the bat. Time for the Ball Tracker. That rolls in and...THREE REDS. The on-field decision has been overturned and Jonny Bairstow is done. Shami has struck again and he continues to bowl in a lethal manner. With that, IT IS TEA ON DAY 1!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, around off, Root pushes this to covers for a quick single.
Back of a length ball on off, Bairstow gets nicely behind this delivery and defends it to the leg side. 50 overs done and we have a little over 2 minutes left in this session.
Bumrah pitches it up and outside, Bairstow attempts a full-blooded drive this time but finds the cover-point fielder. Bumrah has overstepped and it's given as a no ball.
This is excellent batting. Tap and run, that's all they need to do against Bumrah. On a length around off, Joe is forward as he pushes it to cover-point for one.
Fractionally short in length and around off, Jonny taps it down in front of square on the off side and calls his partner for a quick run. A well-judged single.
Bouncer on middle and leg, Jonny Bairstow ducks under it easily.

Smart batting! Bumrah serves a full ball angling in from around off, Root pushes it with gentle hands to cover-point and takes a single. 50th Test fifty for Joe Root and the crowd is on its feet! Superb knock by the skipper but he will be eyeing a big one here.
Short in length and outside off, Root plays late and tries to guide it down to third man but the gully fielder intervenes to stop the ball.
Good leave again from Jonny! Shami delivers an inswinger, lands it on a fuller length outside off, Bairstow once again guards his stumps before making a leave. Excellent battle going on!
Very full and on off, it's pushed back to the bowler.
Shami is trying his best to bowl an outswinger from the middle stump line. Again gets it wrong and ends up slipping a full ball down the leg side. Bairstow tries flicking but misses.
Pitches it up and close to off, shaping away, Bairstow knows where his off stump is and makes a watchful leave.
Shami tries to take the ball away from the batsman, but from the middle stump line, it doesn't move much and Bairstow tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Shami begins his new spell with a gentle outswinger outside off, Bairstow shows no interest in chasing it away from his body.
Mohammed Shami (12-2-15-1) returns.

FOUR! Streaky boundary. Bumrah is bowling with a lot of fire here. Serves a good length ball on off, jagging back in sharply, Root sticks back to defend but it takes the inside edge, beats the stumps and the keeper, before racing away to the fine leg fence.
Sharp delivery! Bumrah delivers it from wide of the crease and fires in a length ball on off, heavy movement on this occasion as Root gets an inside edge onto the pads while trying to defend.
Bumrah was possibly eyeing the blockhole, it's very full around off at 84.7 mph, Root is up the challenge, keeps his eyes on the ball till the last moment and digs it out to covers.
Fractionally short in length and close to off, Root is pushed on the back foot as he plays it down with gentle hands to gully.
Darts in a good length ball on off, Root shows the full face of his bat as he blocks it from the back foot.
Uncomfortable extra bounce. Shortish ball, on middle and leg, Root rises on the back foot to work it across the line but misses. He is hit high on the thigh pad.
Fuller in length and on middle, it's clipped nicely in the space at deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs. 11 from the over, a good one for England.

FOUR! This one is nicer! Siraj continues to be too full with his length, it's around off, Bairstow presents the full face of his bat and unfurls a lovely on drive for a boundary. After that shot, Rahane is placed at silly mid on, at the edge of the pitch.
FOUR! Wow, delightful! Siraj serves a juicy half-volley outside off, Bairstow doesn't takes his front foot forward a lot, relies on his hand-eye coordination and thumps it through covers.
Too full in length on off, speared in, Jonny flicked but found the mid-wicket fielder.

Uppish but safe! Full in length and on middle, angling in, Bairstow probably wanted to flick but is late in closing the face of the bat. It takes the middle portion of his blade and travels uppishly but safely to mid on.
Drifting down the leg side, Root fails to connect with his attempt flick shot and it goes off his pads to the left of the keeper. They cross for a leg bye.
Hurls across a length delivery outside off, angling in, Jonny covers his stumps and shoulders arms.

Shortish ball on middle and leg, Root uses the angle of the bowler and glances it through square leg for a single. The 50-run stand comes up between this pair and it's met with a big round of applause from the crowd.
Good length delivery on top of off, Root remains on the back foot, plays it late and dabs it in front of the slip cordon.
A back foot punch from Root in response to a shortish delivery but again he finds the backward point fielder.
Angles in a fractionally short ball on off, Root sticks on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Back of a length ball on off, Root goes on his back foot and taps it down to backward point.

Jasprit Bumrah is back into the attack. 1/24 off his 10 overs so far. Also, Mohammed Shami is on the sidelines, as the physio is having a look at him. Looks like he is just putting a bandage over his right toe.
A couple to end the over! Short of a length, angling in, on middle, JB hops and works it to fine leg, for a brace.
Short ball around middle, Bairstow ducks under it. Siraj tries to make an eye contact with the batsman with a stare but Jonny is not interested. He walks away.
Fuller on the pads, clipped to deep square leg for a single.
This is an angled delivery, around off, coming in, Joe defends it with ease.
Length and outside the off pole, Joe Root shoulders arms.
PLAY AND A MISS! Full and outside off, Root looks to drive but misses.
Fuller in length, around off, JR pushes this to the left of mid on and they scamper through for a quick run.
Strays and serves a length ball, on the pads, Jonny Bairstow whips this to the right of fine leg for a run.
Another leave as this is bowled on a length outside off.
A carbon copy of the previous delivery.  Bairstow is keeping his calm.
In that zone outside off, JB makes a leave.
Around off, on a length, defended out.
Angled into the middle pole, Joe Root's clip finds the short mid-wicket fielder.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.

Well stopped by Jinx, but he is not able to stop the run. Around off, guided late towards the slip cordon. Ajinkya Rahane, at gully, dives to his left and stops the ball. Root is halfway down for the run and JB responds quickly.
Fires a quicker ball on middle, Root goes back and whips to deep square leg. Hands the strike back to JB.
Nicely played, but just for a run. Slightly short, around off, Jonny Bairstow goes back and hooks to deep square leg. Gets one.
Good length ball, shaping in around off, pushed to mid on.
Mohammed Siraj is back on, replacing Jadeja from this end. This stand has now moved to 41 and India would be feeling a bit of heat.
Outside off, Root leaves it unbothered.

FOUR! Brilliant shot. Confident shot from Root and he is looking good out there. Was not a bad ball from Thakur, it was just some timing from the English skipper. Serves it on a length, on the fourth stump line, it shapes away slightly, but Joe Root is ready and pounces on this to send the ball sailing through covers, for a boundary.
Well played. Outside off, on a length, Root plays this late towards third man, for a couple.

JAFFA! Unplayable. Excellent from Thakur. Even Joe Root had no answers to that. On a length, around off, the ball lands and shapes away beautifully. Joe Root looks to defend inside the line, but the away movement makes the ball whistle past the edge, to the keeper.
Good length delivery, around off, Root looks to push it, but the ball takes the inner half of the bat to roll towards the leg side.
Fuller ball, around off, Joe pushes this to the fielder at covers.
Around off, kept out again by Bairstow.
Gets behind the line of the ball and smothers it out, does Jonny.
Full on off, flighted, JB prods ahead and blocks.
Presses forward to this full ball and defends it to point.
Slower through the air, around off and middle, defended out by Jonny.

FOUR! So nicely played. There was some width and Jonny Bairstow judges this one well, to fetch a boundary. A flatter ball, around off, quicker too, Jonny Bairstow goes back and cuts this behind point and the ball finds its way to the ropes.
On a length close to off, Root allows the ball to come to him and then defends it to the off side.
Uppish but safe! Full and on off, nipping away a bit, Root gets forward to drive but does so uppishly. It though goes safely to cover-point.
In the channel outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Deft! Thakur delivers it on a good length outside off, this time Root waits for it calmly, plays at it very late and just opens the face of his bat to guide it wide of the slip cordon for a boundary. That's his pet shot.
Another length ball close to off, shaping away again, it is defended solidly off the front foot.
A length delivery outside off, Root gets forward and then makes a leave and it shapes away.
Fuller and on middle, Jonny walks down the track and pushes it past the bowler to mid on.

Ooohhh...that didn't miss the outside edge and the off pole by much. A flatter arm ball, on the shorter side around off, Bairstow goes deep inside the crease to force it through the line but misses. It beats the outside edge by a whisker and almost shaved the top of off pole. Jadeja has his hands on his head.

DRINKS BREAK. Jonny Bairstow might have scraped his arm while diving in, and hence, he needs some attention. So, the umpires call for Drinks. Another great hour of cricket between these two sides. India came out of the blocks with intent and their ploy to get rid of Sibley worked, as he gave an easy catch to KL Rahul, who was stationed at short mid-wicket, just after Lunch. Since then, the duo of Root and Bairstow have been watchful and have found it slightly hard to keep the runs coming by, but have not lost their rhythm and have also not tried to force the issue. Bairstow survived a run out scare and would look to make the most of it. India have bowled well, so far, varying their lines and lengths and have kept the English batters guessing, with Shami continuing to trouble them and they will be looking to snare a couple of more wickets before Tea.

BAIRSTOW SURVIVES! The throw comes to the wrong end. A flatter delivery, short and on middle, Root goes on the back foot and works it in front of square leg. They take a single, Jonny wants the second and has come midway down the track. Root shows interest initially but then sends him back and it would have been a simple run out chance had Shami thrown the ball to the keeper. But there wasn't much communication made by the other Indian fielders and Mohammed Shami fired in the throw to the bowler. Jonny gets the chance to rush back and dives to reach the crease as Jadeja aims for a direct hit at the striker's end but misses.
Another one fired in on off, Root defends it from the back foot to point.
Jadeja drags his length back and fires it around off, Joe immediately goes back inside the crease in defense.
FOUR! Crisp! Full and flighted outside off, Root leans into the drive and stylishly caresses it through point for a gorgeous boundary. He is looking very good!
Slower through the air, full and on off, Root drives it off the front foot but straight to covers. Another no ball for overstepping.
Back of a length ball on off, Root goes on his toes and punches it towards point for a run.
Good length ball landing just outside off, moving away off the surface, Root watches it closely and lets it be.
Full and outside off, Root drives it through the line but finds the cover-point fielder.
Shortish and outside off, Root stays back and steers it through point for a couple of runs.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, Root stays on the back foot and plays it down towards backward point.
Play and a miss! Jadeja drags his length short and darts it outside off, Bairstow goes back to cut but misses.
Fuller and on off, once again Bairstow defends it by getting forward.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Loopy and full on off, Jonny strides forward and pushes it to the off side.
Fires a flatter and shorter delivery on middle, Bairstow goes on the back foot and pushes it towards the bowler.
Tossed up again, full and on off, Jonny presses forward and pushes it defensively to the left of the cover fielder. Called a no ball for overstepping.
Starts with a flighted full ball around off, Bairstow leans forward and defends it to the off side.
In the channel outside off, a length ball shaping away, Joe allows it through.
Fuller in length and outside off, Root drives off the front foot but finds the mid off fielder.
Spin time! For the first time in this Test, Ravindra Jadeja has been introduced into the attack!

EDGED BUT SAFE! Shardul gets closer to the off stump line and serves an outswinger on a fuller length, Root tries to drive but checks his shot midway. As a result, it doesn't carry to KL Rahul at gully.
In the corridor outside off, moving away, Root stays back and lets it through to the keeper.
Shardul goes too full and around off, Root drives it to extra cover. Straight to the fielder.
Thakur begins his second spell with an outswinger outside off, still there is some visible movement, Root makes a watchful leave.
Shardul Thakur replaces Shami in the attack. He has bowled 5 overs so far, going for 10 runs.
Ends the over with a bumper on middle and leg, Jonny Bairstow gets low and leaves.
Another solid defense offered by Jonny this time. Has looked solid, so far, has JB.
Way outside off, Jonny Bairstow watches the ball go past him, to Pant.
Jonny Bairstow shuffles to this length ball and blocks it with a straight bat, towards mid on. No is the call for the run, by the English skipper, on the other end.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Gets behind the line of this length ball and defends it out.
Short of a length this time, around middle and leg, Root gets trapped on the back foot and misses his clip. The ball hits the pad and goes towards the off side. Just one from the over!
A misfield and Jonny gets off strike. Fuller in length, around off, pushed back to the left of the bowler and Shami fails to stop it cleanly. One run.
Pushes it on a length this time, does Shami. Just around off and Jonny Bairstow is upto the task, as he defends it out well.
An action replay of the previous delivery. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick to the leg side again and gets hit high on the pad.
Drags his length back and hurls a short of a length delivery. It is around off and is coming back in, JB misses his tuck to the leg side and gets hit on the pad.
In the channel of uncertainty outside off, shouldered arms to, by Jonny.

FOUR! Ends the over on a high. Root plays this shot with so much authority. Siraj overpitches this one, outside the off pole. Joe Root leans into the shot and creams it past the cover fielder and the ball speeds away to the ropes.
Good length delivery, around the off pole, Joe Root presses forward and blocks it well.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Since this is bowled outside the off pole, Root does not go chasing and leaves.
Coming in, from around off. Joe Root blocks it out tentatively.
Mohammed Siraj is into the attack. 1/22 in his 6 overs so far.
Length outside off, Root shows no interest to play at this.
Bowled on a shorter length, around off and middle, pulled away to the left of fine leg for a run.

Drags his length back and serves a back of a length ball, around off, shapes in sharply this time. Root looks to defend, but the ball catches the inside edge, hits the pad, and goes to the leg side. If there was a short leg in place, he would have been interested in taking this catch.
Edgy! Shami is making the batters uncomfortable. On a length again, around off, Joe Root looks to push this through the off side, but the ball takes the inside edge and goes to the leg side.
Just around the off pole, on a fuller length, defended to the off side.
On a length, sliding down the leg side, Joe Root looks to clip it but misses. Rishabh Pant does well to shuffle and pouch the ball.

'WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAITTTT!' is the call by Root and they do not take the single. Fuller, around off, Joe Root comes ahead and pushes this to point. Sends Jonny Bairstow back quickly.
Quicker delivery this time, around off, Jonny knocks this to the mid on fielder.
Fuller this time, outside off, tempts Jonny Bairstow to go for the drive. But JB shows great resistance and lets it be.

FOUR! There were shouts of 'Catch it' but it bounced before the fielder could get there. On a length, on middle and leg, Jonny Bairstow flicks this one aerially through square leg. Mohammed Siraj there dives to his right, but the ball evades him and runs away to the ropes.
Around the off pole, on a length, JB defends this one towards mid on.
A touch fuller, this is the outswinger. Jonny Bairstow dabs this to point and is quick to deny the single again.
Back of a length, around off and middle, Jonny Bairstow goes back and nudges this to short mid-wicket. A loud 'NO!' for the single.
Too full in length and on middle, Bairstow clips it all along the ground in front of square leg for a single.
Fuller in length and outside off, holding its line, Bairstow has nothing to do with it.

Almost another batsman getting caught at short mid-wicket. Good length ball outside off, stopping a bit off the surface, Jonny pushes at it firmly and it takes the inner half of his bat before rolling to KL Rahul.
A length delivery around off, Jonny Bairstow gets on the front foot and blocks it to the off side.
A length ball on middle, the angle of the bowler is taking it down and Root just helps it behind square leg for one.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it watchfully.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Jonny brings down a straight bat in defense towards mid on.
Good length ball on off, defended off the back foot to the off side.
A good length delivery in the zone outside off, Jonny allows it through.
FOUR LEG BYES! A big inswinger again from JB but the line is on middle and leg. Bairstow fails to work it around but this time it takes his pads and beats Pant for a boundary at fine leg.

A muted appeal for a caught behind! Bumrah bowls it with a lively pace, the line though is on middle and leg and it's angling further down. Jonny fails to flick and it clips his thigh pad on its way to the keeper. Pant collects it with a dive to his left but nothing doing.
That is defended solidly off the front foot. End of a successful over from Shami.
Good length ball close to off, Jonny gets forward, plays late with an angled bat and places it wide of gully for a run. Opens his account.
Shami welcomes Jonny with an inviting delivery outside off. He wants to get him driving but Bairstow says, not so early. Leaves it alone.

It is the gingerhead, Jonny Bairstow who walks out now. Has not had the best times facing India in Test cricket. Also, 3 ducks in his last 4 Test innings. Bairstow will be looking to grab this opportunity and redeem himself.

OUT! Caught at short mid-wicket! This was the very reason that fielder was planted at that position and Sibley has walked into the trap. Shami finally has a wicket to show against his name. More than this ball being great, you would have to give it to the planning. A delivery on middle and leg is usually put away easily but probably, India found a weakness with Sibley flicking aerially more often than not. Credit to the analytics team to spot that weakness. Shami just executed the plan and Dominic Sibley clips it uppishly and straight into the hands of KL Rahul. He closed the face of the bat early and played it well ahead of his body. His downfall was inevitable. Early success for India after Lunch.
Commentary.Howout: c KL Rahul b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Good length ball on off, Sibley remains on the back foot and defends it back solidly.
In the channel outside off, on a good length, Sibley shoulders arms after covering his stumps.
A touch short in length and outside off, Root gets back to tap it on the off side. Sibley shows interest in a run but is sent back.

FOUR! Put away and put away in style. Bumrah overpitches outside off, Root leans into the drive, transfers his weight into the shot and crisply strokes it through covers for a glorious boundary. Not many better sights in cricket than watching a well-executed cover drive.
Bumrah targets the off stump with a length delivery, it's angled in and defended from the back foot by the English skipper.
Bumrah shortens his length and delivers it outside off, Root goes on his toes and plays it down to point.
This one is a tempter from Bumrah. He serves it full and outside off, inviting the drive, Root refuses to fall prey to it.
Good length ball on off, Joe prefers to sit back inside the crease as he defends it from the inner half to mid-wicket.
Shami gets greedy here, attempts to bowl an outswinger from the middle stump line. It turns out to be too full and too straight, Root deflects it down to fine leg for a run.
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Jasprit Bumrah. 7-2-16-1 for him so far.
Solidly blocked. A length ball on off, shaping in, Root defends it right under his watchful eyes.
Some movement in the air as a length ball is angled in around middle, Root stands back with an open stance and defends it down with a straight blade.
Back of a length delivery on top of off, Root goes back and plays it late near his body. He opens the face of his bat and taps it down wide of gully.
This time the bowler pulls his length back a bit and delivers it on a good length outside off. It further shapes away from the batsman and Root allows it through.
Shami begins with a delivery on a fuller length outside off, swinging a bit, Root gets forward and plays a mistimed drive to covers.

We are all ready and braced for the second session of play on Day 1. The Indian players make their way out and spread out on the field. Joe Root and Dominic Sibley are out in the middle too. Mohammed Shami to begin proceedings in the post-Lunch session. Here we go...
... DAY 1, 2ND SESSION ...

Going into Lunch, after a shared session, both teams will be relatively happy, however, England would be thinking that they lost one wicket too many. Had they been one down at this moment, that would have got India thinking and reshuffling their plans. Right now, the hosts have Joe Root and Dominic Sibley batting and their plan would be to stitch a solid partnership. Do join us at 12.40 pm GMT (1.40 pm local) for all the action after Lunch.

End of a riveting session of Test cricket! The last ball was a fitting end to the morning session. Nothing much to choose between these two teams. Both fought hard. India drew first blood by removing Rory Burns in the first over itself but then a brave stand between Zak Crawley and Dominic Sibley kept the Indian bowlers at bay. This pair showed a lot of patience and temperament against the moving ball as we witnessed plenty of deliveries beating the outside edge. Although Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Siraj were the bowlers to pick one wicket apiece, it was Mohammed Shami who impressed the most and was unlucky not to get any wickets to his name.

A very loud appeal for LBW but turned down. Oh no...have India lost an opportunity here? The replays show that the wickets were going to be umpire's call. They would not have lost the review, had they gone for it. A length ball, around off, shaping inwards, Dominic Sibley misses to connect his bat with the ball and gets hit on the pad. The Indian players are excited and appeal, but the umpire does not share their excitement as he shakes his head. Now, there is a discussion going on, if they should take the DRS. Jasprit Bumrah seems to gesture that he thinks it is high. Rishabh Pant is in Virat Kohli's ear once again, telling him to go for it. The Indian skipper has a pensive look and decides to let this one go. Had he taken it, would not have made a lot of difference. With that, IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Outside off, on a length, the ball hits the deck and shoots up, as Sibley moves away. Rishabh Pant hops and stops the ball.

BYE. Serves a fuller ball, sliding down leg, Joe Root misses his flick and Rishabh Pant has to dive to half stop the ball. The batters look to steal a bye, as both, Rishabh Pant and Virat Kohli look to chase the ball down. In the end, they come close to picking it up but both of them fail to pick it up. A bye, in the end.
Back of a length, on off, shaping in, Joe Root goes on the back foot and looks to defend. It comes off from the lower half of the bat and bounces past the stumps, towards the slip cordon.
On a good length, outside off, Joe Root watches it sail past him to the keeper.
On a shortish length, outside off, Joe Root seems to be in two minds, whether to leave or to play. Goes for the cut at the last moment but finds the point fielder.
Jasprit Bumrah is back for one final burst before Lunch. 1/16 in his 6 overs, so far.
Sibley leaves this one as well as it was bowled outside the off pole.
Another leave from Sibley as this is bowled outside off.
Fuller outside off, shaping away. Left alone.
Goes for the back of a length ball, around off, DS dabs this to point now.
Another away swinger outside off, the drive is pushed through covers, for a couple of runs.
Fuller, outside off, swinging away, Sibley keeps his wits about himself and leaves.
FOUR! Make that 3 in a row! Root has begun well. On a length, strays too much as he serves it on the pads. Joe Root whips this to deep square leg and gets a boundary.

EDGY FOUR! Mohammed Siraj has his hands on his head. A proper reaction as he just generated an edge off Root's blade. Fuller, around off, Joe Root stays on the back foot and looks to work this through covers. The ball, though, kisses the outside edge and goes aerially through the vacant gully region, to the third man fence.
FOUR! Root is off the mark with a boundary. On a length, around off, Root looks to defend, but the ball takes the toe end of the bat and runs away, past first slip, to the third man fence.

Update - This one is for those who were keeping a close eye on the Women's Hockey at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics. India have been beaten by Argentina in the semi-final and now they will play Great Britain for the Bronze Medal on Friday.
Fuller, but wider outside off. An easy leave for Joe Root.
A short of a length ball, angling in, Root goes back and taps it to point.
Length ball, outside off, Joe Root makes a leave on his first delivery.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away, DS leaves.
Fuller, around off, driven to the point fielder.
Good length ball, around off and middle, defended to the leg side.
An action replay of the previous delivery.
Outside off, length delivery, no shot offered this time.
FOUR! Dominic Sibley does not miss out here. On a fuller length, on the pads, whipped away hard to the deep square leg fence.
Skipper Joe Root arrives in the middle.

Another DRS time! This one is for caught behind. Rishabh Pant has a long chat with Virat Kohli to convince him, Kohli has a sheepish smile on his face as he hesitantly takes the referral. Clear spike and India have a wicket. Well done, Pant!

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! The review works out for India this time and Kohli redeems himself now. Kudos to Virat Kohli and Rishabh Pant. The keeper, as he knew that there was an edge and Kohli, for trusting his keeper and going for the review, even though, just a couple of balls back, a review was wasted on something very similar. Zak Crawley was looking very settled out there, but he has to take the long walk back. Mohammed Siraj has struck and India get another one before Lunch. On a good length, around off, shaping inwards, Zak Crawley looks to defend, but the ball sneaks in, seems to have missed the bat and takes the back pad, on its way to Pant, who takes it. An appeal again, but the umpire is not interested. Pant wants the review, he talks to Kohli and after a brief chat, Kohli goes for it. A brilliant decision, as Ultra Edge shows a clear spike, as the ball passed the inside edge.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary.Commentary: That is defended solidly off the front foot.
On a length, outside off, left alone.
DRS time! Shout for an lbw/caught behind. The umpire has not given it. The Indian players gather and Virat Kohli takes the referral. We hear him saying inside edge. Let's find out.

NOT OUT! The review does not work out for India and they lose one here. They seemed very adamant that this was an inside edge, onto the pads and they felt like this was caught behind. Siraj serves a back of a length delivery, around off, coming in slightly, Zak Crawley looks to defend but seems to have missed it, as the ball takes the pad and goes to Rishabh Pant. A loud appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Virat Kohli is excited and goes for the review straightaway. Replays show that there was no bat there at all. Not even close. Kohli has a wry smile on this face. Time to check for LBW. Ball Tracker shows that the impact was with the umpire's call and it's missing the stumps. So, not only is this not out but the review is also lost.
Angled into the body, Dominic Sibley tucks this to the fielder at fine leg and the strike is rotated.
Slightly behind the good length, outside off, it is moving inwards, but not enough for Sibley to have a poke at this. He shoulders arms.
Full and close to off, shaping away slightly, Crawley plays it late and close to his body as he defends it down towards point.
Back of a length ball around off, Zak walks down the track and offers a straight bat in defense.
A lovely outswinger, on a length around off, Crawley defends it with soft hands to covers.
Good length ball outside off, shaping away, Crawley walks forward, pushes at it and misses.

FOUR! Nice shot! Thakur tries to vary his length and digs in a short ball around off, not much pace and it sits up to be hit, Crawley stands tall and pulls it firmly in front of square leg. It beats the deep mid-wicket fielder to his left and finds the fence.
Fuller in length and around off, Zak drives it through the line but finds the cover fielder. India won't mind Crawley driving with Shardul moving the ball away.
Angling in from around off, on a fuller length, Sibley gets forward and uses his wrists to defend it towards mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, on a length, Sibley shoulders arms.
Pitches it up on this occasion, Sibley uses the angle of the bowler and flicks it to mid-wicket. Can Siraj get one ball to straighten to put a seed of doubt in the batsman's mind?
Slightly short in length and on off, angling in, Sibley hangs on the back foot and defends it down to short mid-wicket.
A bouncer and on middle, Sibley ducks underneath it with ease.
Siraj targets the off stump with his inswinger, around off on a length, Dominic defends it to the off side. Outswinger from one end, inswinger from the other, Siraj and Shardul are doing a good job.
Beaten all ends up! Much better delivery from Shardul, on and around off and from there the ball seams away late, Crawley stands back inside the crease, clueless, as he pokes and misses.
Shardul dishes out a length delivery outside off, moving away off the seam, Crawley has an easy leave. Thakur needs to get his line more towards the off stump.
Quite wide outside off, on a good length and shaping away, Crawley shoulders arms.
On a length and outside off, a scrambled seam delivery, Crawley has a gentle poke inside the line and gets beaten.
Full again, outside off and shaping away a shade, Crawley pushes it off his front foot to the off side, finds the cover fielder.
Fullish and on off, Crawley defends it by getting forward.
Around off on a back of a length, that is defended solidly from the crease to the on side.
Sharp movement for Siraj. It kisses the surface on a good length and nips back in to strike Crawley high on the back leg as he fails to defend. It deflects towards point and they cross for a leg bye.
A length ball on off, Sibley goes back to defend and gets it away off the inside half. The balls rolls behind square leg and they cross.
Nicely played. A length ball on middle, angling in, Sibley closes the face of his bat and works it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Back of a length ball on off, angling in, Sibley goes on the back foot and defends it to short mid-wicket.
Edgy! Siraj brings a length ball into the batsman, big inward movement, Sibley tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and goes to square leg.
Fuller in length and just outside off, nipping away, Crawley lets it go again. A decent start from Shardul.
Good length delivery in the zone outside off, shaping away, Zak walks forward on this occasion before making a leave.
And again. It's too wide outside off, Crawley stays within himself, protects his stumps and allows it through.
Thakur bowls a outswinging delivery but the line starts from outside off, Zak is not going to chase it.
Identical to the last delivery, this time there isn't much movement and Crawley meets it with the full face of his bat in defense.

And Thakur also begins by beating the edge of the bat. Is this bowling end cursed? A lovely outswinger, landing on middle and off and curling away, Zak tries to offer a straight bat in defense but is beaten all ends up.
Ends the over with a bumper, around middle and leg, Dominic Sibley sits under this one and sees the ball sail over him, to the keeper.
Will Mohammed Shami bowl one more over? He has already bowled 7 so far. There is a bowling change, Shardul Thakur gets the chance to show his class.

Some away movement again. Around off, on a length, Zak Crawley dabs this behind point and they take one. Dominic Sibley wanted one more, but seeing the fielder had already reached the ball, they opt against it.
Fired on the pad, Zak misses his attempt to flick. Gets rapped on the pad.
Outside off, length, left alone.

A loud, loud appeal for LBW but looked to be sliding down leg. On a length, around off and middle, angling in, Dominic Sibley misses his tuck and the ball takes the pad and runs through square leg. A leg bye is taken, as an appeal is made, but the umpire shakes his head. The camera pans to Virat Kohli but he does not opt for the review.
Length, outside off, the ball stays a touch low as Dominic Sibley offers no shot.
Length outside off, shaping away. You know what happened, right? It is Shami bowling. So, obviously, Zak Crawley looked to play at it but got beaten. Another great over by Shami!

AND AGAIN! Shami beats Crawley again. Unfortunate that he has not yet removed an English batter. A short of a length delivery, around off, Zak Crawley looks to play this to the leg side, with an angled bat, but the ball beats his bat, to go towards Pant, who collects nicely.
Serves this on a length, on the pads, Dominic Sibley looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and the ball takes the pad and goes to fine leg. They sneak in a leg bye.
On a short length, around off, ZC pulls this one to deep square leg. No timing on this shot and the fielder in the deep gets it on the bounce. One run.

That's a jaffa! Shami has gone past the edge so many times, but he is yet to get a wicket. On a length again, around off, shaping away nicely. Zak Crawley gets beaten yet again as he misses his attempted defensive shot.
Fuller in length, sliding down the leg side, it's left alone.

Drinks break. An absorbing hour of Test cricket. India struck as early as in the first over when Jasprit Bumrah removed Rory Burns for a duck but since then, Dominic Sibley and Zak Crawley have braved the conditions and shown the right application to survive. Bumrah and Shami bowled 6 overs apiece so far and beat the edge on multiple occasions. You can call them a shade unlucky to not pick more than one wicket in the first 60 minutes. Let's see how the next hour shapes up. Here is Mohammed Shami with an extended first spell.
So, 5 runs off Siraj's first over here! Outside off, length ball, Sibley makes a well calculated leave.
Good length ball, around off and middle, clipped to deep mid-wicket and the strike is rotated.
Slightly behind the fuller length, angling in, as it is bowled from wide of the crease. ZC defends it out well.

FOUR! What a shot that is. Cracked it with ease. Siraj serves it slightly more fuller, around off, Zak Crawley swings his blade and creams this one through covers. No point chasing after this. Boundary, it will be.
Same line, but the ball is angled into the right-hander, Zak Crawley pushes it to the left of short mid off, where Jadeja moves and stops it.
Siraj starts off with a length delivery, served outside off, no reason for Zak to play at this, as he leaves.
Here is the first bowling change made by Virat Kohli. ​Mohammed Siraj replaces Bumrah from this end.
Around off, on a length, Sibley looks to push, but only gets an inside edge, on the pad. A good, testing over from Shami!

Hurls across a length delivery, it lands outside off, but nips back in after hitting the deck. It also shoots up slightly, as Dominic Sibley goes back and raises his blade, to allow the ball a safe passage to Rishabh Pant.
Goes fuller on off this time, Sibley dabs this one quickly, to short mid-wicket. KL Rahul quickly gets across it and returns the ball to the keeper.
Fires in a spicy bouncer around off, Dominic Sibley just ducks under this one.
Around the off pole, good length, Dominic Sibley nudges this to the on side.
A touch fuller, outside off, coming in, Dominic Sibley shoulders arms this time.

How has that missed? Bumrah has a smile on his face. He knew how close that was. On a good length, on the fourth stump line, shapes away very late, Zak Crawley shuffles and looks to defend, inside the line, but the away movement deceives him and his blade, as it zips past, to Pant.
Fuller on off, curling in the air, DS taps this one towards covers for a quick run.

Appeal for LBW but looked to be going down leg! Spears in a pacier length ball, on middle and leg, Dominic Sibley comes across and misses his flick to the leg side, as the ball takes the pad and goes to the on side. An appeal, but Bumrah already knew that this was heading down leg, as he gestures the same with his hand.
A slightly behind the good length delivery, around off, angling in, Dominic Sibley looks to play at this, but gets his bat away from the line of the ball, towards the end.
Length and outside off, left alone this time.

Tight single! Is it needed at this stage? No harm done, that is what would please England. On a length, around off, this is nudged to the mid on region. Shardul Thakur runs and collects the ball quickly, as the batters go for the run. Thakur misses his shy at the non-striker's end though. Had he hit, it would have been curtains for Zak.
Outside off, on a length, left alone nicely.
A couple of runs now. Angles in a full length delivery, on middle and off, DS clips this one through mid-wicket. Comes back for the second run, as the man in the deep cleans up.
Shami forces Sibley to play at this and beats him. Good length again, around off, the ball hits the deck and straightens. Dominic Sibley presses forward, looking to defend, but gets beaten.
Length and outside off, Dominic Sibley watches the ball closely and does not poke at this.
Good collection by Rishabh again! Slipped down the leg side, Rishabh Pant dives to his left and does well to pouch this as the batsman lets it go.
On a good length, on off, Dominic Sibley looks to block but misses his attempt. Pant collects it nicely.

Smart from Bumrah. This time, pushes a fuller ball, almost yorker-length, around off, Zak Crawley only manages an inside edge, onto his pad. The ball rolls to the off side, as the Indian players put in a muted appeal, but there was bat there, as clear as day.
Lovely comeback! Bumrah is not letting Zak breathe easy. Angles in a length delivery, outside off, shapes away late, Zak Crawley plays inside the line and gets beaten.

FOUR! That's the second boundary that Zak Crawley has driven to the fence. It looked so good off the bat. On a fuller length, on the fourth stump line, Crawley drives this one through cover-point and fetches a boundary.
On a length outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it for the keeper.
Angles in a length delivery, around off, Zak Crawley dabs this one towards the point fielder. Says no for the single.
Wonderfully bowled! JB runs in and serves from wider of the crease, on a length outside off, Zak Crawley looks to have a poke at this, but the ball whistles past the outside edge, to the keeper.
In the same zone as the last delivery, there is away movement here. Sibley lets it be again.
In the channel of uncertainty, outside off, Dominic Sibley watches it sail past him.
On a length, around off, Sibley looks to defend, but the ball shapes away and goes to point, via the outer half of the blade. He wants one but then denies it, in the end.
FOUR! Dominic Sibley rarely will miss out on a ball on his pads. Gets his first boundary. On a fuller length, on the leg pole, Dominic Sibley clips this one nice to the fine leg fence.
Sticks with the same line, but serves it outside off. Dominic Sibley watches as it is away from him, and makes a leave.

Serves on a back of a length, around off, it is zipping inwards, Sibley looks to work it to the leg side, but misses and gets hit high on the pad. A muted appeal from Shami, but the height would have been an issue there.
Too wide outside off on this occasion and Crawley has an easy leave.

Beaten! Lovely response from the bowler! Bumrah delivers it from wide of the crease and angles in a length ball on off, Crawley tries playing the original line but it straightens to beat the outside edge.

FOUR! Here comes the first boundary of this Test match. Bumrah serves it on a fuller length outside off, Zak Crawley presses forward and unfurls a beautiful cover drive. Jadeja chases it and tries his best to pull it back but fails in his attempt.
Shardul at mid on has been kept busy! Fuller in length on middle and off, Crawley pushes it down the ground and Thakur makes a tumbling stop.
Good length ball around off, angling in, Zak Crawley defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Short in length and wide outside off, Crawley goes on his toes to pull but it takes the toe end and goes towards mid on. Wait is the call as the mid on fielder makes the stop.
Movement is still there, on a length and outside off, Dominic lets it be.
Back of a length delivery around the rib cage, Crawley gets back and gloves it towards fine leg for a run.
In the channel outside off, that is left alone for the keeper to collect.
A pitched up ball outside off, Crawley makes a leave and this one comes back in quite a lot. Pant dives across to his left and does well to make a half stop.
This one is served on a driving length outside off, Crawley takes his front foot forward to cover the line and then makes a stop.
A bouncer from Shami, well-directed, trying to push the batsman back in the crease, Crawley ducks.
Full in length and on off, Crawley clips it through square leg and picks up a single.
Very full in length on off, at 85.6 mph, Sibley brings his bat down and digs it out past the bowler for a single as the mid off fielder cuts it off.
Fullish and on off, at 86 mph, Sibley defends it back to the bowler.
An 89 mph delivery, in the channel outside off, Dominic allows it through to the keeper.

Runs for England! Fuller in length and on off, nipping in sharply. Crawley, who is standing outside the crease, leans across and closes the face of his bat to work it through mid-wicket. By the time the ball is returned, three runs are taken.
Bumrah delivers it on a back of a length and lands it outside off, there is an inward shape but too wide from the batsman to bother him.
Good stop by Shardul! An overpitched delivery on middle, Sibley unveils an on drive and Thakur dives across to his left from mid on to stop the racing ball.
Good length ball on off, angling in, Sibley defends it from the back foot to mid-wicket.
Pitches it up and around off, Zak uses his feet to get down the pitch and pushes it gently in the gap at covers. It's to the left of the fielder and the batsmen cross.
Excellent delivery! Shami delivers a length ball on off, Crawley tries to defend the line but the away movement beats the outside edge. Shami has a big smile on his face, he is loving the conditions.
Fullish and close to off, Zak gets forward to defend but it takes the inner half and rolls to square leg.
Good lines from the Indian bowler. They are operating on and around off. This one though is a bit too wide outside off and Zak makes a leave.
Outside off, on a shortish length, Sibley shoulders arms.

Fuller in length and on middle, defensive push by Crawley down the ground, towards mid on and England open their account with a single. The crowd welcomes the first run of the Test match with a loud cheer.
Bumrah is mixing up his variations well. An outswinger this time, on a fuller length outside off, Zak allows it through.

Big inward swing on this delivery! Fuller in length and around off, Crawley falls over a bit in his stance as he tries to flick. Luckily, he gets it away off the inner edge onto the pads before it rolls to mid-wicket. A muted appeal only by India.
Hurls across a length ball in the channel outside off, Crawley makes a watchful leave after guarding his stumps.
Fuller in length and on off, Crawley defends it quietly to the off side.
In the zone around off, shaping away, Sibley lets it through. Have to say, well left. A maiden from Shami as well!
Shami angles in a length ball around off, some away movement, Dominic opens the face of his bat slightly and pushes it down gently to gully.
Identical to the last delivery but the line is wide outside off, Sibley has an easy leave.
Beautiful! Shami shows his class again with his outswinger, lands it close to off on a good length, Sibley remains inside the crease, feels for it inside the line and gets beaten.
Nice shape on this delivery. Full and angling in around off, it straightens a touch after landing, Sibley is solidly behind the line in defense.
Bowls a good length delivery in the channel outside off, Sibley allows it through.
Fuller in length and wide outside off, Zak Crawley has nothing to do with it as it's too wide. A wicket maiden for Bumrah!
Who will bowl from the other end? It is Mohammed Shami!
Zak Crawley is the number 3 batsman.

OUT! Burns has to depart, a brief appearance for him! This is very smart bowling from Bumrah. He continued to take the last four deliveries away from the left-hander and gets this one to move back in off the seam. Burns remains hanging on the back foot, tries to block this one in a hurry but misses. He is rapped on the pads, the Indians appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Burns is looking nervous as he walks up to his partner and after having a word, he goes for the DRS. The Ultra Edge detects no bat and the Ball Tracker shows that it's the umpire's call on hitting the stumps. Early blow to England.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Time for the DRS! Rory Burns has been given out lbw and he has referred it after consulting his partner. Any bat involved? Pitching outside leg? No bat involved, pitching in line and it's the umpire's call on hitting the stumps. England one down.
Beaten all ends up! Bumrah sticks to his line around middle and off and takes it away with the angle, Burns also decides to remain on the back foot as he pushes inside the line and misses.
Pitches it further up, around middle and off, Rory covers the line and angle before defending it towards mid off.

Bumrah gets close to the off stump line this time, on a length around off, Burns stays back and defends it towards point. So far the ball has gone on with the angle of the bowler, no movement as such.
Bumrah begins with a shortish length ball and angles it away from the southpaw, Burns has a comfortable leave.

Enough of build-up, let's dive in and watch some Test cricket. The Indian players are on the field. Rory Burns and Dominic Sibley are the openers for England. It will be a big test of their skill and temperament. Jasprit Bumrah to kick off proceedings with the new ball. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

Both the teams are out in the middle for the national anthems. It's houseful at Trent Bridge and the atmosphere is brilliant. The English players are sporting a black jersey during their anthem which has a message - Cricket is a game for everyone!
India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma, KL Rahul, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli (C), Ajinkya Rahane, Rishabh Pant (WK), Ravindra Jadeja, Shardul Thakur, Mohammed Shami, Mohammed Siraj, Jasprit Bumrah.
England (Playing XI) - Rory Burns, Dominic Sibley, Zak Crawley, Joe Root (C), Jonny Bairstow, Dan Lawrence, Jos Buttler (WK), Sam Curran, Ollie Robinson, Stuart Broad, James Anderson.

Virat Kohli, the Indian captain, says that they wanted to bat first but they will look to get into the game with the ball and batting in the first hour at Trent Bridge is always tricky. He reckons that if they bowl in the right areas, getting some early wickets will be good. Informs that Shubman Gill is injured and Mayank Agarwal is out of this Test, due to a head injury, sustained in the nets and KL Rahul comes in, at the top. Says that their bowling combination consists of Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammed Shami, Mohammed Siraj, Shardul Thakur and Ravindra Jadeja, who is the spin option for them. Tells that the opportunity to win in England and Australia in the same year is wonderful and they will look to test themselves to the hilt. Kohli says that he is grateful to be playing amongst the crowds now.

Joe Root, the English skipper, calls it a reasonable surface and feels that there will be a little bit of early movement. Wants his batsmen to get a good start and make the most of it later on. Adds that it's always exciting to play in a big series and they hope to perform well. Regarding his team, Root replies that Bairstow returns, Curran returns and it's a very exciting team. Informs that it was a tough decision to overlook Jack Leach. Root opines that you progress as an international player, you gain experience and take into the series and hopes that the players will step up and fill the space that Ben Stokes has left.
TOSS - Both the captains are out in the middle for the toss. Joe Root spins the coin and it looks like he has won the toss. A smiling Root says that ENGLAND WILL BAT FIRST!

Pitch report - Michael Holding says that the pitch looks excellent if you are a bowler. Informs about 10 mm of grass on the surface and tells that you have to dig it to see the soil which looks dry. Feels that as a batter, the ball will come on consistently. Holding says that it is his understanding that India are going to play with just the one spinner. The West Indian is not too sure what the captains would do but opines that if he was the captain, he would bat first and would put runs on the board.

Update from the English camp - We are hearing that Ollie Pope has not travelled with the team to the ground and it's likely that Jonny Bairstow will slot into the middle order. It will be redemption time for Jonny who has 6 ducks against India in Test cricket, of which, 5 have come in the last 7 innings.

Weather - Nowadays, as cricket fans, this update is the most important one. We have seen what happened recently in the T20I series between West Indies and Pakistan. So, how's the weather at Trent Bridge? It's bright and sunny. Clear blue skies with the sun out in its full glory. Looks like a great day for batting.

More impetus for the English Lions, as after they were humbled 3-1 in the 4-game Test series, in India, back in February and March 2021, they would have been looking at this series, as some revenge for what happened earlier in the year. Their team is looking solid and they will need no extra motivation to come out and push India all the way. Joe Root will have to serve his revenge, without his partner-in-crime, Ben Stokes, who has taken a break from cricket, citing mental health reasons (We wish Ben Stokes all the very best and hope he recovers quickly and is back to his best). Sam Curran will definitely have more of a role here, both with bat and ball, in the absence of Stokes. Their batting looks good but will have to show more aggressiveness and also be able to forge good stands, throughout the course of this series. Their bowling department is very much shouldered by James Anderson and Stuart Broad. They will be well partnered by the likes of Mark Wood and probably, Ollie Robinson. Should be interesting to see if they choose to include a spinner as well. It is all building up to be a cracking clash. Toss and team news will be up in a bit.

Let's have a look at India first. After their heartbreaking defeat against New Zealand in the final of the ICC World Test Championship Final, they have had a good break of about a month to mull things over and take a deserved break from cricket to free their minds, before this series. They did take part in a warm-up game and displayed that they are ready to take on the English Lions. Ravi Shastri and Virat Kohli will have a couple of selection dilemmas, as their regular opener, Shubman Gill has been ruled out with an injury. His backup, Mayank Agarwal also suffered a knock on the head and has been ruled out of the first Test. All signs point towards KL Rahul being included, as the opener, opposite Rohit Sharma. Another question that needs an answer is if both Ashwin and Jadeja will be paired together, or an extra pacer will be included in the team, at the expense of one of these two.

Greetings, ladies and gentlemen! It is time. It is FINALLY time for one of the most awaited Test series between two heavyweights of international cricket. England and India are ready to lock horns in a 5-game Test series and it is time for the first duel between these two at Trent Bridge. This series also is the launch of the 2021-2023 World Test Championship cycle and what a first game we have on our hands, aye?
.... GAME DAY ....
Right then. The Indian players have made their way out in the middle. Followed by the opening pair of England, Rory Burns and Dominic Sibley. Jasprit Bumrah to start with the ball.

England were quick enough to end things in the second session. But it was not a top performance in the field for them. Root will see to it at they change it next time around. Ollie Robinson was the pick of the bowler for them as he picked up a fi-fer. He was well supported by James Anderson who took a four-fer. They will be pretty happy with their effort with the ball. The England players have a huge task in their hands. They will aim to not loose quick wickets and preserve them till the end of the day.

India started off on a good note! Their openers gave them a solid start, But after Rohit Sharma fell, the Indian top-order faced a collapse and they founf themselves four down in no time. And once Pant fell, early on in Day 3. It was the partnership of Rahul and Jadeja who made sure to take the team to safer shores. Rahul fell short of his century, as he got skittled out for 84. Then Jadeja took the charge and played an important knock. But, in the end it was the tail-ender who whacked their tails and took India to a comfortable position.

Well, the tail-enders made sure to end the innings on a high. This last wicket partnership came out of nowhere and England were as shocked as the rest of the world. Bumrah and Siraj helped India to get a lead of 95 runs, this will surely get the Indian camp happy.

OUT! CAUGHT! No the tail-enders could not swell the lead to 100. And finally England are successful to end things here and Ollie Robinson gets his fi-fer. A full length ball, on off. Bumrah looks to go big yet again. But this time he does not connect well. The ball takes the top edge and goes towards fine leg. Stuart Broad covers a lot of ground to his right. He take a good running catch. India end their innings on 287 and they lead by 95 runs.
Commentary.Howout: c Stuart Broad b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: Two more. A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple. They lead by 95 runs now. Can they make it 100?
A length ball, on off. Bumrah throws his bat at it. He lofts it over the cover region for a couple.
Hurls a length ball, around off, nipping in. Bumrah looks to whack it across the line but misses.
Starts this over with a slower one. Robinson serves it full and outside off. Bumrah looks to chase it but misses.
Anderson serves a length ball, outside off. Siraj looks to push it away but misses.
A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah flicks it through mid-wicket for another single.
A length ball, around off. Siraj looks to work it across the line, but the ball takes the outside edge and meets the fielder at third man on a bounce. They take one.
Outside off, Siraj looks to heave it away but misses.
A good length delivery, on off. Siraj lifts it over the cover region. The balls lands in a vacant region. The batters take a couple.
Anderson serves a  length ball, around off. Siraj moves back and looks to work it on the off side but misses.

FOUR! England continue to leak runs here. A short ball, on middle. Bumrah looks pull it away. The ball hits the top edge and flies over the keeper's head for a boundary. Jasprit Bumrah is enjoying his batting here.
A short ball again, outside off. Bumrah looks to go after it but misses.
A back of a length ball, around off. Bumrah sways away from the line of the delivery.
Back of a length ball, on off. Bumrah looks to pull it away but misses.
A slower length ball, on off. Bumrah plays it across the line and works it towards mid-wicket.
A full length ball, on middle. Bumrah drives it through mid on for a couple.

LEG BYE! A fuller length ball, around leg. Bumrah looks to flick it away but misses. The ball clips the pads and rolls to the off side. The batters take a risky single and the umpire signals a leg bye.
A length ball, around off. Bumrah stays back and looks to heave it away but misses it completely.
A length ball, outside off, Bumrah looks to go after it but misses.

FOUR! EDGY! A full length ball, on off. Bumrah looks to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and flies over the slip cordon. It ends up in the boundary at third man. So, 14 runs coming off the first three deliveries.

SIX! It's gone all the way. Curran serves a short ball, on off. Bumrah rocks back and pulls it over the square leg fence for a maximum. This is most likely the highest number of runs for Bumrah in Test cricket.
FOUR! Now Bumrah is taking the charge now. A full length ball, on the pads. Bumrah tucks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Welcome boundary! A full length ball, on off. Robinson bowls it in the slot. Siraj stands tall and drills it through mid off for a boundary.
A length ball, around off pushed to covers.
A length ball, on the pads. Siraj looks to flick it but misses. The ball clips the pads and goes towards the keeper.
Who will walk out next? It is going to be Mohammed Siraj, the last man to walk in.
Will England take the second new ball? Yes, they will. Ollie Robinson to steam in with the new ball.

OUT! TIMBER! The new ball does the trick for Ollie Robinson. Robinson serves a full length ball, on middle. Shami looks to defend it out but misses. The ball hits him in the pads and goes onto rattle the stumps. Shami was looking really good in the middle, he did enough to survive for so long and add some crucial runs to swell the lead. India lead by 62 runs.
Commentary.Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary.Commentary: A touch short, on the pads. Shami looks to flick it away but misses and get hit on the pads.
A length ball, outside off. Shami looks to push it away but misses.
Good leave. A length ball, outside off. Bumrah looks to defend but pulls his bat back.
Curran serves a full length delivery, outside off. Moving across the batsman. Bumrah looks to defend it out but misses.
